==English==
{{Bible|35|Nahum|Zephaniah}}

===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] [[Habacuc]], from {{Hebr.}} [[חבקוק|חֲבַקּוּק]] (Ḥavaqqūq or Ḥăḇaqqûq) a prophet of the Old Testament and Jewish Tanakh. The name comes either from the Hebrew word [[חבק]] ''habhak'' meaning "embrace" or else from an [[Akkadian]] word ''hambakuku'' for a kind of plant.

===Proper noun===
'''Habakkuk'''

# A [[prophetic]] [[book]] of the [[Bible]]; the thirty-fifth book in the [[Old Testament]] or the eighth part of the [[Tere Asar]] in the Jewish [[Tanakh]].
# A [[Jewish]] [[prophet]] of the Old Teatament; author of the book that bears his name.
# A rare [[given name]].

